You are an expert full-stack developer building the Cuemath AI Tutor Screener.

## What this project is
A browser-based voice interview system. A tutor candidate speaks via microphone,
an AI interviewer responds via synthesized voice, and at the end a structured
assessment report is generated across 5 dimensions: clarity, warmth, patience,
simplification ability, and English fluency.

## Tech stack
- Backend: Python 3.11 + FastAPI + uvicorn + groq + python-dotenv + pydantic v2
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite + axios + react-router-dom v6
- Voice input: Web Speech API — SpeechRecognition (Chrome Desktop only, non-continuous)
- Voice output: Web Speech API — SpeechSynthesis (built-in, all browsers)
- LLM: Groq API, model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile, OpenAI-compatible endpoint
- Deployment: Railway (backend) + Vercel (frontend)

## Folder structure — never deviate from this
backend/
  main.py              ← FastAPI app entry, CORS config, router registration
  routers/
    chat.py            ← POST /api/chat
    assess.py          ← POST /api/assess
  services/
    groq_client.py     ← Groq API wrapper, all LLM calls go here
    prompts.py         ← All system prompts as constants, never inline in routes
  models/
    schemas.py         ← All Pydantic models for requests and responses
  .env                 ← NEVER commit. GROQ_API_KEY and ALLOWED_ORIGINS live here
  requirements.txt

frontend/
  src/
    pages/
      Landing.jsx      ← Entry screen, mic permission, start button
      Interview.jsx    ← Live interview, voice loop, turn counter
      Report.jsx       ← Assessment report display
    components/
      VoiceRecorder.jsx    ← SpeechRecognition: start/stop/result/error
      AIVoice.jsx          ← SpeechSynthesis: speak text, onend callback
      StatusIndicator.jsx  ← Visual state: idle/listening/processing/speaking
      RubricCard.jsx       ← Single dimension in the report
    hooks/
      useInterview.js  ← Interview state machine (the core hook)
      useSpeech.js     ← Abstracts VoiceRecorder + AIVoice together
    api/
      client.js        ← axios instance with VITE_API_URL base URL
      interview.js     ← postChat(messages) and postAssess(transcript) functions
    App.jsx
    main.jsx

## Coding rules — follow all of these exactly
- Functional components and hooks only. No class components.
- async/await everywhere. No .then() chains.
- All FastAPI route handlers return a typed Pydantic response model.
- All API keys in backend .env only. Frontend has VITE_API_URL only.
- CORS: explicitly list allowed origins. Never use allow_origins=["*"].
- State management: useState + useReducer only. No Redux, no Zustand, no Context.
- No database, no ORM. Session state lives in React only (array of message objects).
- All frontend API calls go through /src/api/interview.js. Never raw fetch in components.
- Error handling: all FastAPI errors return {"detail": "..."}, frontend shows detail to user.
- CSS: plain CSS files per component. No Tailwind (no build step available).
- Imports: use @/ alias for src/. Max 2 levels of relative imports.

## Critical technical constraints — these will break the app if ignored
- SpeechRecognition: set continuous=false (NOT true). Restart a fresh recognition instance
  each time the candidate should speak. Continuous mode causes compounding transcript bugs.
- Groq free tier: 6,000 TPM and 1,000 RPD. Keep total tokens per /api/chat call under 800.
  This means: concise system prompt (~300 tokens) + last 4 messages only (not full history).
- Groq endpoint: https://api.groq.com/openai/v1 (OpenAI-compatible, use openai Python SDK)
- SpeechRecognition only works on Chrome Desktop. Show a browser warning on other browsers.
- SpeechSynthesis must be triggered inside a user gesture handler (button click) the first
  time it is called, otherwise browsers block it silently.
- Interview turn limit: exactly 7 AI turns. Do not let it run longer.
- Assessment call is a single request at the end. Response must be valid JSON only.
  If Groq returns non-JSON, retry once with a stricter prompt before showing an error.

## Anti-patterns — never do any of these
- Never set recognition.continuous = true
- Never send the full conversation history to Groq (token limit)
- Never put GROQ_API_KEY in frontend env or any JS file
- Never use an ORM or database
- Never import API calls directly in page components (goes through /api/ only)
- Never use .then() when you can use await